    <p>While dig­i­tal in­clu­sion often be­gins with ac­cess to de­vices – it is not the end so­lu­tion. With­out enough sup­port and pro­grammes to build ca­pac­ity, the de­vice may end up be­ing used wrongly or be a white ele­phant.</p>
    <p>DR PANG, who was among ex­perts who said it is im­por­tant to build dig­i­tal lit­er­acy among those from low-in­come back­grounds, so that they know how to use tech­nol­ogy to add value to their lives.</p>


